WEBVTT

00:01:59.889 --> 00:02:01.904
including my own father,

00:02:01.928 --> 00:02:05.896
and most recently, a former colleague
who died at 41 from bowel cancer.

00:02:07.392 --> 00:02:09.666
We started having
open and frank conversations

00:02:09.690 --> 00:02:11.245
about what we were experiencing.

00:02:12.027 --> 00:02:14.487
We talked about the practical stuff,

00:02:14.511 --> 00:02:16.225
the stuff no one prepares you for:

00:02:17.098 --> 00:02:19.136
dealing with government agencies,

00:02:19.160 --> 00:02:21.214
hospitals, nursing homes,

00:02:21.238 --> 00:02:22.876
advanced care directives,

00:02:22.900 --> 00:02:24.333
funeral directors

00:02:24.357 --> 00:02:27.055
and extended family members,

00:02:27.079 --> 00:02:28.652
(Laughter)

00:02:28.676 --> 00:02:31.062
making decisions about coffins,